Site.Name: WABASH RIVER AT NEW HARMONY, IN

SiteVisit.WeatherDescription: clear, cool, no precip, light wind, swirling/variable
SiteVisit.Comment: Due to GOES issue, DCP swap (DAA is now stage only sensor, Satlink2 is main DCP) and missing data, stage values are uncertain during this visit. Stage was reset around 1730 but uncertain of the exact correction...previous applied shift of 0.10 was carried forward to account for some error. Orifice is possibly unstable due to "jumping around" of stage. Stage used for QM are computed values. Major siltation of QW sondes. Nitrate out of water. Missing data from 10/24-10/25/2018 due to decodes issue. Decodes fixed early on 10/25/2018 and data returns. Available EDL has been added to account for the GOES issue beginning on 10/21. There is no EDL for the remaining gap.

MonitorInspection.Comment: Sonde was covered in heavy silt when removed from pipe. It does appear that the sonde was in the water but lower part of pipe is covered in mud. Nitrate is out of water and cannot be lowered any more unless the cable is changed. Movement by field techs in the mud caused high turbidity values. Turbidity from the cross section read ~18-20FNU. Field turbidity and site are influenced by plumes it was nearly impossible to not disturb the mud when taking readings. After cleaning readings from both the site and field sonde were taken from the boat. DO probe swapped (GOAP out, WABASH in). Missing data due to GOES issues and DCP swap.
MonitorInspection.FieldMeterComment: Field readingss taken from the boat near end of pipes. Tried to clear mud around the ends of pipes but it won't last.

StreamFlowControlInspection.Comment: some tree debris on L & REW. Very low flow.

DischargeMeasurement.Comment:
QRev - Moving-Bed Test 10/26/2018 11:46:11: - Loop closure error. Very low stage and velocities, moving bed is very unlikely. Will still use BT as reference.
